<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3037467307" pageId="42" pageNumber="42">12 females (AMNH *265968, *265972, *267067, *267383, *267388, *267845, *267848, *267849; MNHN *1995­854, *1995­855, *1995­856, *1995­857) and 13 males (AMNH *265969, *265971, *267065, *267066, *267068, *267387, *267844, *267846, *267847; MNHN 1995­858, *1995­859, *1995­860, *1995­861); see table 8 for measurements. One individual of unknown sex (AMNH 266978) was recovered from the crop of a bat falcon (see Field Observations).</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
